researchAreas:
- id: 1
  title: Visuo-Tactile Sensing
  description: Developing high-resolution, multimodal visuo-tactile sensors to provide
    robots with human-like sense of touch for complex manipulation tasks.
  image: https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518770660439-4636190af475?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=800
- id: 2
  title: Dexterous Manipulation
  description: Creating algorithms and control strategies for multi-fingered robotic
    hands to perform intricate tasks such as in-hand manipulation and tool use.
  image: https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1589254065878-42c9da997008?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=800
- id: 3
  title: Embodied AI & Teleoperation
  description: Building systems for intuitive human-robot teleoperation and collecting
    high-quality embodied data to train robust robotic policies.
  image: https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1485827404703-89b55fcc595e?auto=format&fit=crop&q=80&w=800
openings:
- id: 1
  title: Ph.D. Students (Fall 2026)
  type: Ph.D. Program
  description: We are looking for highly motivated Ph.D. students to work on dexterous
    manipulation, tactile sensing, and embodied AI. Strong background in robotics,
    machine learning, or mechatronics is preferred.
  requirements:
  - Bachelor's or Master's degree in CS, EE, ME, or related fields.
  - Strong programming skills in Python and C++.
  - Experience with ROS, PyTorch, or robotic hardware is a plus.
- id: 2
  title: Postdoctoral Researchers
  type: Postdoc
  description: Seeking postdoctoral researchers with a strong publication record in
    top robotics/AI venues (ICRA, IROS, RSS, CVPR, NeurIPS) to lead projects in visuo-tactile
    manipulation.
  requirements:
  - Ph.D. in Robotics, Computer Science, or related fields.
  - Proven track record of high-quality publications.
  - Ability to mentor junior lab members and lead research projects.
- id: 3
  title: Research Assistants / Interns
  type: Internship
  description: Undergraduate and Master's students are welcome to join the lab as
    research assistants. You will work closely with Ph.D. students on cutting-edge
    robotics projects.
  requirements:
  - Self-motivated and passionate about robotics.
  - Basic programming skills and willingness to learn.
  - Commitment of at least 15 hours per week.
